  <info>
    <h3><strong>Introduction</strong></h3>
      
      <p> The study of ornithology is vast and multidisciplinary in essence. Thus this "Ornithometrics" (<i>*ornitho-*</i>; 'bird' and <i>*-metric*</i>; 'relating to measurement') will refer to the collection of measurements that can be taken from birds. The headings of the <a href="#toc">table of content</a> were made to facilitate navigation, but some packages might fall in multiple categories. Other <i>task views</i> could be consulted for broader coverage of topics including ecology and environment (<view>Environmetrics</view>) and spatial analysis (<view>Spatial</view>).
      </p>
      <p> Some packages might require specific R versions or RStudio versions. 
      </p>

