    <section id="moveco">
      <h3><strong>Movement ecology, navigation, telemetry, GPS, RFID, habitat use</strong></h3>
        <strong> Relocation of animals: </strong>
        Finding the location of animals can be done via a diversity of methods such as Very High Frequency (VHF) radio waves emitters, Global Positioning System (GPS), semi-automated data collection using <a href="https://motus.org"> MOTUS Wildlefe Tracking System</a> and other techniques. It is recommanded to look at the <i>"Space and habitat use characterization"</i> section of the <view>Tracking</view> to learn about <i>Home ranges,</i> <i>Habitat use,</i> and <i>Non-conventional approaches for space use.</i> I. Bartomeus <a href="https://gist.github.com/ibartomeus/cdddca21d5dbff26a25e">has a page</a> in which preference indicies calculations in R are demonstrated.
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/steffilazerte/cavityuse">Determine cavity use from geolocator light data</a></li>
          <li><pkg>ctmm</pkg>:  (Calabrese, Fleming and Gurarie 2016)</li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/animalnexus/feedr">feedr</a></li>
          <li><pkg>nicheROVER</pkg>:  <a href="https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/nicheROVER/vignettes/ecol-vignette.html">Guide for using nicheROVER</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/cppeck/razimuth">razimuth</a>: (Gerber et al. 2018)</li>
          <li><pkg>ResourceSelection</pkg>:  (Lele and Keim 2006; Lele 2009; Sólymos and Lele 2016)</li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/jmsigner/rhr">rhr</a>: reproducible home range analysis with R (Signer and Balkenhol 2015)</li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/johnbaums/rmaxent">rmaxent</a></li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/cran/sigloc">sigloc</a>: The sigloc (Signal Location Estimation; Berg 2015) package is now <a href="https://cran.r-project.org/package=sigloc">archived</a> on the CRAN. </li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/MotusWTS/motus">Motus</a>. The Motus book can be <a href="https://beta.motus.org/MotusRBook/">seen from this link</a></li>
        </ul>
    </section>

